-- Inter Beats Tottenham in Champions League; Manchester Utd., Barcelona Win
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-10-20T20:44:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-20/inter-beats-tottenham-in-champions-league-manchester-utd-barcelona-win.html
Inter Milan held on to defeat 10-man
Tottenham 4-3 in soccer’s Champions League.  Samuel Eto’o scored two goals, while Javier Zanetti and
Dejan Stankovic had one each, as defending champion Inter took a
4-0 halftime lead in the Group A game in Milan. Gareth Bale
scored all three goals for Tottenham, which had goalkeeper
Heurelho Gomes sent off with a red card in the eighth minute.  FC Twente and Werder Bremen tied 1-1 in the other Group A
match, while in Group B, Schalke defeated Hapoel Tel-Aviv 3-1
and Lyon beat Benfica 2-0.  Manchester United beat Bursaspor 1-0 and Rangers tied
Valencia 1-1 in Group C. Barcelona defeated Copenhagen 2-0 and
Panathinaikos drew 0-0 with Rubin Kazan in Group D.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  